object.doc: Represents a cost or price of invoiced service.
Class used for amounts in zero InInvoices
Points to VAT used in this price.
Points to OutInvoiceAmounts in which this cost was use
A list of prices invoiced for this item.
Points to an executed item from a customer's order which expected price was invoiced as this price.
Abstract class representing an executed item which corresponds to services accomplished by deliverers for our customers. It can be registered in a customer order.
One way association.
Points to a price in Navision buffer.

Represents invoice amount from the Navision buffer.
For more detail see "Navision buffer documentation".
For internal invoices this is the invoice amount which generated this invoice amount.
If this invoice is for internal company unit then it points to a real cost from an internal incoming invoice which was created upon this price.
